  "texts": [
    "As noted, participants rated the computergenerated responses as higher quality along virtually every dimension tested.",
    "Importantly, these quality ratings were made before revealing that some of the passages were computer-generated, increasing their objectivity.",
    "This project represents a first foray into the ordinary perceptions of LLM discourse about moral questions.",
    "Several limitations stand out as fertile areas for future research.",
    "First, our test did not support a reciprocal extended or open-ended dialogue as might occur in a traditional Turing Test."
